description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to join our Resuscitation &amp; Simulation Team as a Resuscitation &amp; Simulation Trainer, in a permanent post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This varied and stimulating role encompasses basic and immediate levels of resuscitation training, simulation teaching and point of care education. our main focus is patient safety and quality improvement; planning, delivering and implementing excellent standards of care through education. if you are an organised, motivated individual who strives for high standards and has a passion for education and teaching, we would encourage you to apply for this post and join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this fantastic opportunity, please call the Resuscitation and Simulation office area Q and speak with the team for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training to gain the relevant resuscitation qualifications in the elements of the essential criteria within the person specification will be supported once appointed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post go on the NGH street - click on working lives - work for us -view all jobs and apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jo Rainsley, Job title: Resuscitation and Simulation Manager, Email address: joanne.rainsley@ngh.nhs.uk, Telephone number: 01604 544981,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Walker&lt;/p&gt;
